"{\"uid\": \"chicago.suntimes.com-columnists-2024-07-30-olympics-opening-ceremony-controversy-last-supper-lgbtq-religious-right-greek-mythology\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Why are we asking for donations?Why are we asking for donations?This site is free thanks to our community of supporters.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 120, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Voluntary donations from readers like you keep our news accessible for everyone.Donation Options  Search  Search  Search  Tristan Tate holds a picture of a scene that took place during the Paris Olympics opening ceremony that seemed to evoke Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper,\\\" during a protest Sunday near the French Embassy in Bucharest, Romania.\", \"from\": 121, \"to\": 472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 243, \"end\": 250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tristan\", \"score\": 0.9999999981978362, \"rank\": 1.8004853625204297e-09, \"text\": \"Tristan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tristan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tristan\"}, {\"begin\": 251, \"end\": 255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\", \"score\": 0.9999998787716395, \"rank\": 1.207181690298726e-07, \"text\": \"Tate\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\"}, {\"begin\": 363, \"end\": 380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6346425173381177e-19, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 453, \"end\": 462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bucharest\", \"score\": 0.9999999999727152, \"rank\": 2.7124926799070646e-11, \"text\": \"Bucharest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bucharest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bucharest\"}, {\"begin\": 464, \"end\": 471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"score\": 0.9962697941860416, \"rank\": 0.0037310717209713077, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Andreea Alexandru/Associated Press  Share  Generally, I tune out the Olympics.\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 552, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the past 206 weeks I have not thought about competitive swimming.\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Why start now?\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 637, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I do like pageantry.\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So my wife and I watched the opening ceremonies Friday, a rolling street party with boatloads of athletes floating down the Seine, waving happily.\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 810, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 788, \"end\": 793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.1225080784237578e-12, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremonies were lauded.\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 839, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A daring feat,\\\" The Washington Post gushed.\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 857, \"end\": 876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.7435656289850214e-35, \"text\": \"The Washington Post\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Paris transformed into a spectacular stage.\\\"\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 930, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 886, \"end\": 891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999754436, \"rank\": 2.4751549389841293e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We found the opening dull.\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 958, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It must be dramatic if you are there,\\\" my wife kept saying, trying to give them the benefit of the doubt.\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 1066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To me, it seemed like standard Cirque du Soleil street theatrics with a few celebrity cameos thrown in, though I am willing to assume the fault is with me.\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like \\\"The Bear,\\\" the opening ceremony is something everybody loves, but I just do not get.\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1313, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Have you ever been to an Italian beef joint?\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1340, \"end\": 1352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_beef\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Italian beef\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_beef\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_beef\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Did you see a dozen people in the back, \\\"yes chef\\\"-ing each other?\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1426, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I just did not buy the premise.)\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1459, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Internalization of dislike - my negative reaction is my problem, not yours - is an important, though rare, survival skill.\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A more popular route is to become offended, get ruffled, register displeasure and try to rearrange life to suit your whims.\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1707, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A path I just do not understand.\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1740, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You go over someone's house and do not like the wallpaper, you do not then take your fingernails and try to claw it down.\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1862, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Who does that?\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1878, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A lot of folks.\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1895, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"People are constantly getting offended and registering that offense.\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1964, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremonies, which I shrugged off,drew howls of condemnationfrom the religious right.\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 2061, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Last night's mockery of the Last Supper was shocking and insulting to Christian people around the world,\\\" Speaker Mike Johnson, R-Louisiana, announced on X. I could give another dozen examples.\", \"from\": 2063, \"to\": 2257, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2134, \"end\": 2143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9873497703711578, \"rank\": 0.012812308257242591, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As you may have heard, they were wrong - even though the scene involved people at a table, the opening ceremony's artistic director has said it was supposed to be a Greek bacchanalia - Greece being the place where the Olympics originated.\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2424, \"end\": 2429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.9954168040922259, \"rank\": 0.004570272307373361, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2444, \"end\": 2450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.997062089378279, \"rank\": 0.0029464299594716466, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(The local Olympic committee, nonetheless, felt compelled toapologize.)\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France is a truly secular society, as opposed to the lip service we settle for here.\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2571, \"end\": 2577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999663366876881, \"rank\": 0.0002909459177590722, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French do not need to mock Christianity.\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 2700, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2660, \"end\": 2666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.999999175794413, \"rank\": 5.358989918137381e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2687, \"end\": 2699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999903575372, \"rank\": 9.594147939936145e-09, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have done one better - they have exiled it from its position astride the body politic.\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2792, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's against the law to wear a cross to public school in France - or a yarmulke, or a burqa, I hasten to add; do not want to get anybody into a quivering funk thinking they are being singled out.\", \"from\": 2793, \"to\": 2988, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2850, \"end\": 2856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999663366876881, \"rank\": 0.0002909459177590722, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Being offended is a symptom of the egoism pandemic in American society.\", \"from\": 2990, \"to\": 3061, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3044, \"end\": 3060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.990141051303, \"rank\": 0.009957115386739412, \"text\": \"American society\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course the tableau is mocking you - who else in the world is there?\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3132, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Writing a newspaper column as I do, I continually hear from the offended.\", \"from\": 3134, \"to\": 3207, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many simply present the simple fact of their offendedness, as if nothing more need be said.\", \"from\": 3208, \"to\": 3299, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your column offended me, sir.\", \"from\": 3300, \"to\": 3329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Period.\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3337, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"So do something about it\\\" is unvoiced.\", \"from\": 3338, \"to\": 3381, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Though I am not sure what I am supposed to do.\", \"from\": 3382, \"to\": 3428, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Apologize, I suppose.\", \"from\": 3429, \"to\": 3450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Recant.\", \"from\": 3451, \"to\": 3458, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Because they are offended.\", \"from\": 3459, \"to\": 3485, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not do that.\", \"from\": 3487, \"to\": 3504, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What I want to say is: \\\"Why are you telling me this?\", \"from\": 3505, \"to\": 3557, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I wrote the damn thing.\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3581, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yesterday.\", \"from\": 3582, \"to\": 3592, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I believed it then, and believe it even more now, and so should you.\\\"\", \"from\": 3593, \"to\": 3662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes I write back, \\\"I am not responsible for what you choose to be offended by.\\\"\", \"from\": 3664, \"to\": 3749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just to rattle 'em.\", \"from\": 3750, \"to\": 3769, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If they are a scornful Trumpy - are there any other kind?\", \"from\": 3770, \"to\": 3827, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- I might type out an email along the lines of, \\\"You know, the opinion of someone in thrall to a liar, bully, fraud and traitor does not carry the weight you seem to imagine it does.\\\"\", \"from\": 3828, \"to\": 4011, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then I delete the email before sending - usually, anyway, because any reply from me is something they can wave over their heads as further reason to be offended.\", \"from\": 4012, \"to\": 4173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A better reply is, \\\"But I did not write it for you.\\\"\", \"from\": 4175, \"to\": 4227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Robert Crumb, the great underground cartoonist, has a wonderful line: \\\"Not everything is for children.\", \"from\": 4228, \"to\": 4330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4228, \"end\": 4240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Crumb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Robert Crumb\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Crumb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Crumb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not everything is for everybody.\\\"\", \"from\": 4331, \"to\": 4364, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I wish we could splice the \\\"This is not for me,\\\" gene into the public brain.\", \"from\": 4365, \"to\": 4441, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It would save a lot of wasted time.\", \"from\": 4442, \"to\": 4477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I suspect many people secretly enjoy being offended.\", \"from\": 4479, \"to\": 4531, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They do it enough.\", \"from\": 4532, \"to\": 4550, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There must be a kind of high.\", \"from\": 4551, \"to\": 4580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They put the thing that supposedly offends them in a bag and huff it.\", \"from\": 4581, \"to\": 4650, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have a number of readers who despise what I do, supposedly, yet are here every single blessed day, reading it and writing me three emails a day telling me exactly how awful I am.\", \"from\": 4651, \"to\": 4831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Or at least I suppose that's what they are saying.\", \"from\": 4832, \"to\": 4882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not as if I open their emails gathering dust in my spam filter.\", \"from\": 4883, \"to\": 4952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ignoring stuff you do not like is an important life skill.\", \"from\": 4953, \"to\": 5011, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Give it a try.\", \"from\": 5012, \"to\": 5026, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Share  Chicago Sun-TimesColumnist  \\u00a9 2025 Chicago Sun-Times Media, Inc.\", \"from\": 5028, \"to\": 5099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5035, \"end\": 5042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"score\": 0.9999999966958057, \"rank\": 3.3042922062004324e-09, \"text\": \"Chicago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\"}, {\"begin\": 5070, \"end\": 5087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago_Sun-Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chicago Sun-Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago_Sun-Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago_Sun-Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Terms of Use\\u2022Privacy Notice\\u2022Cookie Policy\\u2022Terms of Sale\", \"from\": 5101, \"to\": 5156, \"entities\": []}]}"